{New} Naked Burgers + Chunky Salsa 🍅🌱🧄

To be completely transparent, I'm not a huge burger person...I mean, I'll eat one at a BBQ or party where they're being served...but it's not something I'd personally choose.

THESE Naked Burgers are a different story though...full of fresh herbs, feta, and grated zucchini that gives em' SO MUCH FLAVOR 🤤 The grated zucchini actually keeps your burgers moist, so they never come out dry!

These juicy, tasty burgers topped with salsa just speak my love language!

Try them out while zucchini & tomatoes are ripe and plentiful!

makes about 4 servings

Ingredients:
1 small zucchini, grated 
1 lb lean ground beef or turkey 
2 cloves garlic, pressed or minced
2 Tbsp freshly chopped parsley
2 Tbsp freshly chopped mint
1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese
1/2 tsp sea salt
1/4 tsp freshly ground pepper
1 Tbsp olive oil, avocado oil, or cooking oil spray

For your chunky salsa:
1 cup ripe tomatoes, chopped
1/2 red onion, diced
a handful of fresh cilantro leaves, chopped
1 fresh lime, juiced
1/2 tsp sea salt

Optional:

large lettuce leaves to serve the burgers

Instructions:

In a medium mixing bowl, combine all of your ingredients for the salsa, then set aside.

Grate your zucchini and squeeze out much of the moisture (discard), then place zucchini into a large bowl.

Add in ground meat, garlic, all fresh herbs, crumbled feta, sea salt and pepper, then stir well to combine(I like to just get my hands in there to combine well).

Take about 2 large spoonfuls of your mixture and form into a burger patty, then with your thumb gently press into the middle (this helps the center cook evenly). Repeat with remaining meat.

Heat a large skillet over medium heat and drizzle with oil.

Add in the patties, and cook for about 3-4 minutes on each side, or until done to your liking. (If using ground turkey, your burger must be cooked thoroughly).

To serve, add lettuce leaves on a plate, then add your burger on top.

Add a spoonful or two or chunky salsa and enjoy!

❤Rachel

{NEW} Tuna Cucumber Party Bites 🥒🍋🌱
Maybe you're like me and have lots of canned tuna or salmon in the pantry? (Yep. This recipe works with salmon too!)

Maybe you're also looking for a way to turn that canned fish into a super tasty, quick lunch or snack for your family this summer?

This is the PERFECT recipe to use up those garden cucumbers you may have on hand!

A DELICIOUS and unique lunch, snack or party appetizer idea! 

I made up a quick batch of these over the holiday weekend for our entire crew, and they were gone faster than anything I've made in quite a while!

Total crowd pleaser! 

I think these would also be awesome with shredded chicken or flaked salmon instead of tuna if that's what you have at home, so experiment and find your FAVORITE way to make em'!

12 bites about 3 servings

Ingredients:
1 large English cucumber
2 (5 ounce) cans or pouches, wild caught tuna, drained well
2-3 Tbsps plain Greek yogurt, or to taste
1/2 tsp smoked paprika
1/4 tsp sea salt, or to taste
1/8 tsp black pepper, or to taste
3 Tbsps chopped chives
1/2 a fresh squeezed lemon + zest

Instructions:

Partially peel the cucumber, then using a sharp chef's knife carefully cut into 1/3-inch slices. You should have about 24 slices.

In a bowl, add your tuna, yogurt, paprika, sea salt, pepper and chives.

Using a microplane, grate half of a lemon, the juice it over the tuna.

Mix until the tuna salad mixture is well combined.

Lay half of the cucumber slices on a large platter, and add small spoonful of your tuna salad onto each. Top with the remaining cucumber slices. 

Insert skewers into the middle of each one for easier serving, as shown in the video. 

Enjoy!

❤Rachel

Avocado Chicken Salad 🍅🌽🥑
Here's a SUPER Simple Dinner, or meal prep idea for you!
.
Do you know how to pick and store a PERFECT Avocado?🥑
We're going to chat about this in my IG "stories" tonight!🙌
.
makes 4 servings

Ingredients:
1 lb. boneless skinless chicken breasts
1 Tbsp ghee/clarified butter
2 cups cherry tomatoes, quartered
2 avocados, cubed
1/2 cup fresh or frozen organic corn, cut from the cob 
1 medium red onion, thinly sliced
a handful of fresh cilantro leaves, chopped
juice of 1 large lime
1 Tbsp extra virgin olive oil
sea salt and fresh ground black pepper, to taste, about 1/4 teaspoon each 
Instructions:

Melt ghee in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add in the chicken and season with sea salt and pepper. 
Sear for about 4 minutes on each side, or just until cooked through and no longer pink in the inside. 
Set your cooked chicken aside on a cutting board to rest for a few minutes, then using a sharp knife cut it into bite sized cubes.

In a large bowl, add in your cubed chicken together with tomatoes, avocado, onion, cilantro and corn.

Squeeze fresh lime juice over and drizzle with olive oil. 
Toss gently to combine, then taste test, and season with sea salt and pepper to taste.

Enjoy! ❤Rachel
.

{NEW} Quick-Pickled Cucumber Salad🥒🥒🥒 All about those FAST + TASTY recipes lately!

We had this Salad alongside salmon and brown rice the other night, and it was THE PERFECT simple meal!👌 makes about 4 servings

Ingredients:
1 large English cucumber
1 small red onion, peeled and halved
1/3 cup rice vinegar, or apple cider vinegar 
1/4 cup warm water, filtered 
1 Tbsp maple syrup or raw honey
1/2 tsp sea salt
1/4 tsp chili flakes 
Instructions:

Using a sharp knife, carefully slice your cucumber into 1/8-inch-thick slices.

Thinly slice the red onion. 
In a medium glass bowl, whisk together the vinegar, water, maple syrup or honey, sea salt and chili flakes.

Place the sliced cucumber and onions into a clean 17oz. wide mouth glass jar.

Pour in your vinegar mixture, and make sure the veggies are completely submerged.

Seal with it's lid, then refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

Serve and enjoy! 
Your pickled cucumber salad will keep well refrigerated for up to 5 days and it will actually taste better after a couple of days. ❤Rachel

Ok...this is the BEST thing I've done in quite a while!
So, you may know that I have a very large blended family...4 kids of my own, 2 more are Jason's. They are all teenagers and often have friends over for sleepovers on the weekends.

Welp. That's A LOT of people to cook breakfast for! Sometimes 10-12 people!

I learned about cooking eggs THIS wsy, and I've since perfected my technique!

Here's what I also did to EASILY feed my crowd:
I set out 8-10 slices of nitrate-free Canadian bacon on another large, greased sheet pan + sliced Ezekiel English muffins sliced in half on another.
Basically I've figured out how to cook 8-10 Egg Muffins using all 3 of th racks in my oven all at once!
I add the Canadian bacon + sliced English muffins during the last 5 minutes of eggs cooking.

Let me know if you try-out this idea, and how it works for YOUR crowd! 
Quick + Easy Sheet Pan Eggs for a Crowd!

makes 6-8 servings

Instructions:
12 free range eggs
1 1/2 Tbsps avocado oil, or olive oil
sea salt and fresh ground black pepper, to taste

Optional: garnish with spices of choice like chili flakes, dried oregano, parsley etc.

Ingredients:
Preheat a 11x17 inch rimmed baking sheet in your oven at 425 degrees f.
Yes. You really preheated the pan too.

Meanwhile very gently crack your eggs into a large measure cup.

Once your oven + pan is hot and reaches 425, carefully remove pan from your hot oven (using proper hot pads) and carefully drizzle pan with oil. Coat well.

Gently pour in the eggs and spread them out onto your hot pan. 
Careful not to break yolks...but its OK if a few do break.

Season with sea salt and pepper to your taste. 
Cook in the preheated oven for 8-10 minutes. (some ovens are hotter the others so you should check them out at about 5 minutes, and depending on your egg preference, you may want to cook longer). Slice eggs up as shown and enjoy immediately! ❤Rachel

Tangy Grass-fed Beef Lettuce Wraps + Avocado Cilantro Cream Sauce 🥑🌞🍅 

{ I figure we still have a good 8 weeks or more for eating Dinners on the patio, and outdoor entertaining.
Let's enjoy it as much as possible, while keeping things SIMPLE with THESE delicious wraps! }

makes about 4-5 servings

Ingredients:
1 lb. grass fed ground beef
1 Tbsp avocado oil, or olive oil
1/2 yellow onion, diced
2 cloves fresh garlic minced
1 yellow bell pepper, diced
1 tsp smoked paprika
1/2 tsp ground cumin seed
1 tsp oregano
1/2 tsp chili powder
sea salt and freshly ground black pepper, to your taste
1 jalapeno, sliced
1/2 cup chopped cherry or grape tomatoes

butter lettuce leaves for serving 
Avocado Cilantro Cream Sauce:
1 very ripe large avocado
1/2 cup plain Greek yogurt
1/4 cup packed cilantro with steams
1 jalapeno diced
juice of 1/2 fresh lime
1/2 tsp garlic powder
sea salt and freshly ground black pepper, to your taste

Instructions:
Place all avocado sauce ingredients into a blender or food processor and process until smooth. Transfer to a bowl, cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

Heat oil in a large skillet over medium high heat. Add onions and bell peppers; cook for 3 minutes. Add fresh garlic and all seasonings, then saute for about 1 minute, finally add the ground beef.

Brown beef, while crumbling, & stirring occasionally for about 5 minutes until cooked through.

Serve beef mixture over lettuce leaves topped with chopped tomatoes, sliced jalapeno and a drizzle of your avocado cilantro cream sauce. 

Enjoy!
❤Rachel

Shrimp + Pineapple Salsa Bowls🍤🍍🌶

We've been enjoying tropical fruits these past few weeks at our house because I've noticed they're plentiful at our local grocers right now. On sale too!

Make these bowls for dinner tonight, or make them for future meals this week - either way you're making THE RIGHT choice 💯

These Shrimp bowls are packed full of our FAVORITE ISLAND flavors while providing an awesome blend of macronutrients and micronutrients!

I think these Shrimp + Pineapple Salsa Bowls are just the thing we require to give us that nice steady energy to FUEL our day while simultaneously being SUPER delicious!

Although fresh pineapple is available year round in most of the US, this island fruit hits its peak from March through July.

Besides being completely DELICIOUS, fresh Pineapple is packed with nutrients, antioxidants and other helpful compounds, such as enzymes that can help with digestion, fight inflammation and disease. So eat up!

I'm thinking that adding diced avocado immediately before serving would be ABSOLUTE PERFECTION on top of these bowls!🥑

These meal prep bowls stay good for up to 3 days in the fridge, and are great eaten cold. I love to heat mine up, including the salsa and stir everything together then enjoy.👌

4 servings

Ingredients:
2 cups cooked brown rice, or quinoa 
1 Tbsp avocado oil, or olive oil, or unrefined coconut oil 
1-1/2 lbs. peeled and deveined shrimp 
sea salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste

For salsa:
2 cups diced fresh pineapple
1 medium sweet red bell pepper, diced
1 small red onion, finely diced 
1/2 cup chopped fresh cilantro leaves 
1 small jalapeño pepper, finely diced (optional, adds heat)
2 Tbsps fresh squeezed lime juice 

For the dressing:
1/2 cup coconut yogurt, or plain Greek yogurt 
2 Tbsps fresh squeezed lime juice
1 tsp chili flakes
1 tsp fresh lime zest, or to taste 
2 cloves fresh garlic minced, or 1/4 tsp garlic powder
1/4 tsp sea salt, or to taste 
1/8 tsp ground pepper, or to taste

Pink Smoothie Bowls 🍨🍌🍓

Make restaurant worthy smoothie bowls at home with just a few simple ingredients.

The perfect recipe idea to use up all those ripe Summertime fruits!

What is a smoothie bowl?

Smoothie bowls are great for breakfast during the warmer months, or a hearty snack/treat anytime.

A smoothie bowl is a smoothie eaten from a bowl with a spoon instead of drinking it from a cup. 

The cool thing is that we can add toppings to smoothie bowls for added textures, flavors, and nutrients! Because of this, smoothie bowls can be a bit more satisfying.

You can easily add in some protein powder or collagen to really increase the protein intake of your bowls (which I totally recommend).

➡️ Rachel's Tip:

Smoothie bowls you can buy in a restaurant or shop are often marketed as healthy, but LOADED with added sugar and made with pre-made, processed ingredients and artificial purees. So this is a great reason to make your own smoothie bowls at home with real frozen fruit and ingredients you love!

Ingredients:
4 ripe peaches, peeled and chopped small 
2 cups ripe strawberries, halved
2 large bananas, peeled and sliced small 
2-3 Tbsps coconut water, coconut milk, or water

garnish ideas: fresh berries, sliced banana, coconut flakes, granola, chopped nuts, nut butter, chia seeds, hemp seeds, etc.

Instructions:

Line 2 medium baking sheets with parchment paper.

Place your prepared fruits onto the baking trays and freeze for at least 4 hours or overnight.

Ingredients:

Instructions: 
Preheat your oven to 425 degrees f. then line 2 large baking trays with parchment paper.

Lightly press any remaining seasonings into your zucchini as your removing them from the bowl.

Divide the coated zucchini rounds between the trays leaving space between each, then bake for 8-10 minutes, or until zucchini is tender crisp.

node.text:
Marinated Radish + Carrot Salad 🌱🥕

Thinly sliced radishes & carrots are marinated in a delightfully tangy homemade dressing for an hour or two. The salad is cold and crisp, with tons of flavor thanks to the veggies soaking up the bright homemade dressing. 

This Salad is PERFECT to prepare ahead of time, and simply pull it out of the fridge to serve once you're ready to eat. EXCELLENT for parties & BBQ'S.

This is one of my favorite types of recipes because it's really simple, yet it's very unique and impressive. You'll receive lots of compliments for your creativity!

🍋 ALWAYS use freshly-squeezed lemon juice from an actual fresh lemon. Bottled lemon juice from the store will give your salad a strange metallic or overly acidic taste.

🕊 Make SURE that you actually love the taste of the olive oil that you use for your homemade dressings because your salad will come out tasting very much like the oil you use (each oil has its own unique flavor).

6 servings

Ingredients:
1-½ lbs radishes
1/2 pound medium carrots
4 green onions
1/4 cup fresh cilantro leaves 

For the dressing:
fresh lemon zest from 1 large lemon 
3 Tbsps freshly squeezed lemon juice
1 Tbsp apple cider vinegar
2 Tbsps raw honey
2 Tbsps extra virgin olive oil
sea salt and ground pepper, to taste, about 1/4 teaspoon each 

Instructions:

Start by preparing your veggies: very thinly slice the radishes and carrots (a good mandoline makes this job easier), chop the green onions and cilantro. 

Add them all into a large bowl.

In a small jar, add all of your dressing ingredients and vigorously shake to emulsify. Or whisk them really well in a small bowl.

Pour your dressing over your prepared veggies and toss well to combine. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour up to overnight.

Enjoy!

❤Rachel

Coconut Cream Mousse 

This Coconut Cream Mousse recipe is delicious, refreshing, and so pretty!

Top with your favorite berries and it’s the perfect summer dessert!

Have you ever made your own whipped coconut cream? You're in for a treat!

It’s fluffy, all-natural, and dairy-free making it the perfect treat or dessert.

Always chill your coconut cans in the fridge overnight. The coconut cream solids will rise to the top of the can in the fridge, leaving the coconut water on the bottom. You’ll need this concentrated cream found on top in order to create your fluffy coconut whipped cream. Once your cans have chilled in the fridge OVERNIGHT, then you're ready to make your treat.

🍯 The sweetness factor is such a PERSONAL preference, so please consider this when adding in the stevia, honey, or maple syrup. Depending on your taste, you may want a bit more or less.

6 servings

Ingredients:
4 x 13.5 oz cans coconut milk
pinch of sea salt
2 tsps vanilla extract
8-10 drops of liquid stevia, or 2 Tbsps raw honey or pure maple syrup, or to taste 
fresh lime zest as garnish 
fresh mint leaves as garnish 
2 cups fresh raspberries for serving 

Instructions:

Your coconut milk needs to be refrigerated overnight prior to preparation.

Carefully open the coconut milk cans. Use a spoon to skim off the thickened top layer into a mixing bowl.

Reserve the watery liquid at the bottom to use for another purpose such as smoothies or lemonades.

Add the sea salt, vanilla, and stevia over the coconut cream into the bowl.

Use an electric whisk and beat the coconut cream for a few minutes, or until it resembles whipped cream.

Serve immediately in small cups or jars topped with fresh berries as shown, then garnish with freshly grated lime zest and mint.

Enjoy!

❤Rachel

Crockpot Pineapple Chicken 🍍

Absolutely Delicious *tender* Pineapple Chicken prepared in my most favorite kitchen appliance: the crockpot. The Slow Cooker does the work and we don't need to babysit!

Sweet & Tangy homemade pineapple sauce, made of fresh pineapple, coconut aminos, fresh garlic, and fresh ginger. VERY simple, but so good you'll be making this sauce often!

If you're looking for something SUPER satisfying to easily feed your crew this week - We've got you covered!

Serve over cauliflower rice, quinoa, or brown rice and alongside steamed broccoli, but don't forget a good sprinkle of chives or scallions!

Crazy GOOD! Works extremely well for meal prep too! Store leftovers in sealed meal prep containers for up to 3-4 days in the fridge.

We've been enjoying tropical fruits this past month at our house because I've noticed they're plentiful at our local grocers right now. On sale too!

Although fresh pineapple is available year-round throughout most of the US, this island fruit hits its peak from March through July.

Besides being completely DELICIOUS, fresh Pineapple is packed with nutrients, antioxidants, and other helpful compounds, such as enzymes that can help support digestion, fight inflammation and disease.

🍍So eat up!

6-8 servings

Ingredients:
1 ripe pineapple
2.5 lbs boneless skinless chicken breasts or thighs, chopped into ½ -inch pieces
1 cup chicken stock or bone broth
6 oz tomato paste
1/2 cup coconut aminos tamari, Braggs liquid aminos, or low sodium soy sauce 
3 fresh garlic cloves, minced
1.5 inch thumb-sized ginger, minced or 1 tbsp ginger paste
black or white ground pepper, to taste, about 1/4 teaspoon 
cooked brown rice, quinoa, or cauliflower rice to serve
fresh chives, or parsley to garnish

Instructions:

Cut and peel your pineapple, remove the core and chop in into ½-inch pieces.

Add half of your fresh pineapple chunks into a blender. Add in the chicken broth, tomato paste, coconut aminos, garlic, ginger, and pepper. Blend until smooth.

Super Easy Homemade Refrigerator Pickles 🥒🥒🥒 

There's nothing quite like Fresh, Crisp Homemade Pickles!

If you're a pickle lover like me, then you gotta try making your own this Summer!

I really like knowing what ingredients are actually going into my pickles, especially since the cucumbers soak up all of that stuff!

Conventional cucumbers are in the top 10 for high pesticides, and are on the Environmental Working Group's "Dirty Dozen" list, designed to help us quickly decide which produce should be purchased USDA organic. 

I completely recommend that the cucumbers you buy be organic, or local garden grown for homemade pickle making if you're able to find them. 

makes 3 jars of pickles 

I used 3, 16 ounce / pint jars

Ingredients:
6 cloves fresh garlic, peeled
6 springs fresh dill
15 medium cucumbers, rinsed, halved or quartered lengthwise
1 large carrot, peeled halved, the cut in quarters on lengthwise

To make the brine:
2 cups distilled water
1 cup apple cider vinegar
1 Tbsp whole black peppercorns 
1 Tbsp mustard seeds
1 tsp fennel seed
2 Tbsps kosher or sea salt

Instructions: 
Start with sanitizing the jars. Bring a large pot with water to the boil, and carefully place in your jars and lids. Boil for 5 minutes, then carefully take them out from the water and set aside.

Next, whisk all brine ingredients into a saucepan and bring to a boil.

Once boiling, remove from the heat and set aside.

Allow to cool. Whisk this cooled brine together one last time immediately before adding into your jars.

To assemble your pickle jars, divide the garlic and dill equally among 3 mason jars. 
Add in the cucumbers and carrots as shown, then fill the jars with brine, making sure you completely cover the veggies with your brine.

Seal your jars and refrigerate.

You'll have delicious homemade pickles ready to be served in about 10 days.

Store them refrigerated for up to 2 months.

Enjoy! 

💚Rachel

Quick & Easy Zucchini Beef Skillet 🍅

Okay, people...THIS SUPER QUICK Skillet Meal is EXACTLY what you're going to want to make when all those ripe vegetables start showing up in our gardens and farmers markets! 

Just 20 minutes, and a few SIMPLE ingredients is all you need, and you'll have a DELICIOUS dinner on the table - FAST!

makes about 4 servings

Ingredients:
1.5 lbs grass feed ground beef
3-4 cloves fresh garlic, minced
1 yellow onion, diced
2 different color bell peppers of choice, seeded & chopped
3 medium zucchini, halved and sliced
1.5 cups cherry or grape tomatoes, halved
sea salt and fresh ground black pepper, to taste 
a small handful of fresh herbs like parsley, cilantro or basil, chopped to garnish

Instructions:

Heat a large skillet over medium high heat and cook your ground beef breaking it into small pieces with a wooden spoon as it cooks.

Once browned and cooked through, drain the excess grease, then add in your garlic, onions, peppers, zucchini.

Lower heat to medium, and continue to cook stirring frequently for about 6 minutes, or until veggies are crisp tender.

Stir in your cherry tomatoes and remove from heat. Season with sea salt and pepper to your taste.

Garnish with fresh chopped herbs if desired and enjoy! 

❤Rachel

Protein Packed Breakfast Egg Wrap

Everyone's always asking for new breakfast ideas 💡  Breakfast egg wraps are great if you need something really fast & GOOD to make for yourself. And you know what?! This doesn't need to be reserved only for breakfast time - these wraps make for a satisfying meal anytime!

Thanks to the high quality protein, veggies, and healthy fats, we will feel satisfied for hours!

➡️How To Make Oat Flour

Oat flour is the simplest flour to make at home, using whole rolled oats (old-fashioned oats) and your high-speed blender or food processor.

2 cups of whole rolled oats equal about a cup of oat flour, or maybe a bit more, depending on how finely you grind it.

You may have to stop your machine and move the flour around with a spoon.

Process for at least 1 minute. You want your flour to be as finely and uniformly ground as possible.

➡️ 17 Reasons to Eat Eggs Everyday:
https://cleanfoodcrush.com/17-healthy-reasons-to-eat-eggs/

1 serving

Ingredients:
1/2 tbsp olive or avocado oil
2 large eggs
2 Tbsps milk of choice
sea salt and ground pepper, to taste
2 Tbsps oat flour, or ground oats
1 thin slice cheddar cheese, cut in half 
2 thin slices nitrate-free deli turkey
1 tomato, thinly sliced
avocado, thinly sliced
1/2 cup fresh spinach

Instructions:

Heat the oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.

In a medium bowl, whisk your eggs together with the milk, sea salt, and pepper. Add the oat flour and whisk well to combine

Pour your egg mixture into your hot skillet and tilt the pan to evenly coat the bottom; Cook for 3-5 minutes, or until the bottom is lightly browned and the center is set. Flip your wrap and cook for 1 minute more.

Once it’s done cooking, slide it onto a plate. Immediately top with cheese, fresh spinach, tomato slices, deli turkey and avocado. Roll up, cut it in half and serve!

Enjoy!

❤Rachel

Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Balls ❤🍪

Add cookies into the daily mix = Because we all need some daily YUM 🍪🥛🍪🥛 

I love to keep a batch of these in the fridge for the kids to snack on after school!

"I was SO happy when I realized I had all the ingredients to make these. Made them this evening and oh my goodness.... oh my goodness, they are yummy!"
- Jennifer Evan's

makes about 22 balls, 1-2 cookie dough balls is considered one serving 

Ingredients:
2 cups almond flour
1/2 cup coconut flour
1/2 cup natural peanut butter
1/2 cup pure maple syrup
1.5 Tbsps unrefined coconut oil, melted 
1 tsp vanilla extract
1/4 tsp sea salt
1/3 cup mini dark chocolate chips

Instructions: 
In your food processor, place all of your ingredients and process until well combined.

Scrape down the sides and process again just until it starts to resembles crumbled cookie dough.

Line a sheet pan with parchment paper. 
Take a spoonful of mixture and roll it between your palms to create a ball, as shown.

Repeat with remaining mixture.

Place the balls into the prepared sheet pan and refrigerate for up to 1 hour.

Transfer to an air-tight container and keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

Enjoy! 

❤Rachel
